  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Immigration Removal Centre - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_immigration_removal_centre">Immigration Removal Centre</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_justice_organisation">Justice Organisation</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_immigration_removal_centre">Immigration Removal Centre</xref>
 is a place where people are held:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>whilst immigration requests are being processed</p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>whilst appeals against removal are being processed or</p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>pending deportation after having had asylum applications refused.</p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
For further information on Health and Justice healthcare, see the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nhs_england">NHS England</xref>
 website at: 
              <xref href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/commissioning/health-just/"
               scope="external"
               format="html">Health and Justice</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
